         <notesStmt>
            <note type="summary">
               <p>This is a letter from William J . Thompson (1861-1929), registrar general, to Robert Chalmers (1858-1938), under-secretary for Ireland. Thompson became chairman of the census committee in 1911 and worked in the office of the registrar general until 1926. Chalmers became under-secretary for a brief period following the resignation of Matthew Nathan (1962-1939) in the aftermath of the 1916 Rising. 
The letter states that for the information of the Lord Lieutenant Ivor Guest (1873-1939) there is a number of enclosures regarding the amount of Irish citizens who left the Port of Ireland since 1915. It also states that information regarding emigration since 1895 is enclosed.</p>
            </note>
         </notesStmt>
         
