             no. 4/M/214.  General Register Office,<lb/>Charlemont House<lb/>Dublin    6th June, 1916    Sir,   I beg to forward herewith for the consideration of His<lb/>Excellency, the Lord Lieutenant, a Return of the Number of<lb/>Emigrants (Natives of Ireland) who left the Ports of Ireland<lb/>during the first five months of each of the years 1915 and 1916,<lb/>and also a copy of a Table showing the Number of Emigrants in<lb/>each month from the 1st January, 1895.  I send also a Return showing, by Provinces, the Religious<lb/>Professions of the Emigrants (Natives of Ireland) who left the<lb/>Irish Ports during the month of May, 1916.  Duplicates of these Returns are enclosed.  I am, Sir,<lb/>Your obedient Servant,   William J Thompson <lb/>Registrar General.  The Under Secretary<lb/>&amp;c., &amp;c.,<lb/>Dublin Castle.  
            <pb n="2" facs="L1916_1913_img_1364_2"/>
             EMIGRATION STATISTICS, IRELAND.  <!-- A five columned table follows showing this data.-->RETURN showing, by Provinces, the Religious Profession of the Emigrants (Natives<lb/>of Ireland) who left Irish Ports during the month of May, <!-- The word May is handwritten --> 1916.  <!-- The number 6 is also handwritten --><row role="label"> <cell role="data"> <cell role="data">Month <!-- All the data recorded in this table is from May 1916 --></cell> <cell role="data">Province</cell> <cell role="data">Number of Emigrants <!-- This cell is subdivided into Religious Profession and Total sub cells --> <cell role="data">Religious Profession. <!-- This cell is subdivided into two following cells Roman Catholic and All Other Denominations --> <cell role="data">Roman Catholic</cell> <cell role="data">All Other Denominations.</cell> </cell> <cell role="data">Total</cell> </cell></cell></row><lb/><row role="data"> <cell role="label"> </cell> <cell role="label">Leinster<!-- All the Provinces are typed --></cell> <cell role="data">46</cell> <cell role="data">17</cell> <cell role="data">63<!-- The totals in the table are all handwritten --></cell> </row><lb/><row role="data"> <row role="label">May <!-- May is handwritten --> <row role="label">Munster <row role="data">84 <row role="data">6 <row role="data">90 </row><lb/><row role="label">1916 <!-- This is handwritten --> <row role="label">Ulster <row role="data">73 <row role="data">77 <row role="data">150 </row><lb/><row role="label"> <row role="label">Connaught <row role="data">184 <row role="data">4 <row role="data">188 </row> <row role="label">Total of Ireland <row role="label"> <row role="data">387 <row role="data">104 <row role="data">491 </row> </row></row></row></row></row></row></row></row></row></row></row></row></row></row></row></row></row> <table></table> <!-- This is a typed note underneath the table-->N.B. —The figures relating to the Religious Profession of Emigrants can only<lb/>be regarded as approximate, as it has been ascertained that Religious Profession is<lb/>not one of the particulars entered on the contract tickets or manifest lists of<lb/>vessels bound for the U. S. of America, <seg type="del">and that at Queenstown the rush of Emigrants<lb/>is so great that it is not possible for the Enumerator in many instances to interrogate<lb/>them regarding their Religious Profession.</seg>  William J Thompson <!-- This is a handwritten signature --><lb/>Registrar-General.   General Register Office,<lb/>Charlemont House,<lb/>Dublin, 6<hi rend="superscript">th</hi> June <!-- 6th of June is handwritten --> 1916. <!-- 6 is handwritten -->   <seg type="unclear">Handwritten initials EOJ</seg>     (1826.) Wt. 6043—34 / 142.100.12 / 15. A. T. &amp;Co.,Ltd. 
